This paper is about deep learning models and their parameterization. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the redundancy in the parameterization of deep learning models and how to predict the remaining values. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The third likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as deep learning is widely used in computer vision tasks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper discusses neural networks and their parameterization. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper discusses the optimization of deep learning models.
